The 	extbf{Web connector} does not automatically handle REST API pagination with token-based mechanisms. Custom logic in 	extbf{M-code} must be implemented to iterate through pages using the 	exttt{nextPageToken} field. This is a core requirement for consuming paginated APIs that return more records than the per-request limit.

	extbf{Statement 2 — Option A Analysis — INCORRECT}
While creating separate queries for each page is theoretically possible, this approach is manual, not scalable, and violates best practices. Creating 49 individual queries (24,500 ÷ 500) would be error-prone, extremely difficult to maintain, and represents a non-professional solution. Manual pagination is not a viable strategy for production data pipelines. Additionally, this approach cannot dynamically adapt to changes in token values between refreshes.

	extbf{Statement 3 — Option B Analysis — INCORRECT}
	extbf{Basic Authentication} requires username and password credentials, which is incompatible with 	extbf{API key authentication}. These are distinct authentication methods. Additionally, 	extbf{Power Query does not have} a built-in automatic pagination feature for REST APIs with token-based continuation. Scheduled refresh only controls when queries run, not how paginated data is retrieved. Pagination logic must still be implemented in M-code.

	extbf{Statement 4 — Option C Analysis — INCORRECT}
This endpoint is explicitly a REST API (indicated by the 	exttt{https://api.company.com/v2/orders} URL structure and 	exttt{nextPageToken} pagination mechanism), not an OData feed. REST APIs and OData are distinct protocols with different response structures and query mechanisms. The 	extbf{OData connector} cannot be used to consume a generic REST API endpoint. Using the incorrect connector type would result in connection failure or data retrieval errors.

	extbf{Statement 5 — Option D Analysis — CORRECT}
Option D implements the correct approach for paginated REST APIs in Power BI:
 egin{itemize}
  \item 	extbf{Custom M-code loop:} Dynamically constructs URLs using 	exttt{nextPageToken} from each response, eliminating manual query creation and automatically adapting to token changes.
  \item 	extbf{Response concatenation:} Properly combines paginated results from all iterations into a single dataset.
  \item 	extbf{Error handling and retry logic:} Implements exponential backoff or request throttling to respect API rate limits and avoid connection failures due to rate limiting.
